terms: Once a seat becomes available, and you are first on the waitlist, you will be automatically added to the class.
If you no longer want the class, you must remove yourself from the waitlist.
If you are registered for another section of the same class (and it is a 'non-R' suffix class) it will be dropped if the waitlisted section is added.
You can only waitlist one section of the same class (except R suffix classes).
Waitlisting does not guarantee that you will get a seat in the class.

You will be skipped in the waitlist if you have registration holds, if adding a class will cause you to go over the maximum credit hour limit (undergrad: 18.0), or if you do not meet other class limitations (e.g. majors only, etc.).
Waitlisted classes will be added even if there is a time conflict with another class in your schedule.
waitlistInfo.note: Waitlists expire at the end of the 4th calendar day after the beginning of a semester or term, and you will be removed from all waitlists.
